"use strict";(self["webpackChunkiacss"]=self["webpackChunkiacss"]||[]).push([[5399],{5399:function(e,a,t){t.r(a),t.d(a,{default:function(){return d}});var i=t(3396);const s=(0,i.uE)('<div class="view-container" data-v-01e38c87><div class="view-title" data-v-01e38c87>Abstract Submission</div><div class="view-main" data-v-01e38c87><div class="view-section-title" data-v-01e38c87>Abstract Submission Guidelines</div><p data-v-01e38c87>Abstract submission is through EasyChair platform, exclusively. Authors must use an existing EasyChair account or create a new one. Information on how to create an EasyChair account can be found <a href="https://easychair.org/help/account_creation?a=" target="_blank" data-v-01e38c87>here</a>.</p><p data-v-01e38c87><strong data-v-01e38c87>In case you cannot successfully submit on EasyChair platform, please mail: <a href="mailto:zhang_hui@zju.edu.cn" data-v-01e38c87>zhang_hui@zju.edu.cn</a> or <a href="mailto:iacss.2025.tgu@gmail.com" data-v-01e38c87>iacss.2025.tgu@gmail.com</a> .</strong></p><div class="view-section" data-v-01e38c87><div class="view-section-title small" data-v-01e38c87>Step 1</div><ul data-v-01e38c87><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Enter/create your EasyChair account</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Once you have the account, please use this <a href="https://easychair.org/my/conference?conf=iacss2025" target="_blank" data-v-01e38c87><strong data-v-01e38c87>link</strong></a> to get access to the conference.</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Click “make a new submission”</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Fill out the abstract form and press the ‘Submit’ button below.</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>The deadline for submission of abstractions is April <s data-v-01e38c87>15</s> 30, 2025 at 23:59 AoE (UTC-12).</p></li></ul></div><div class="view-section" data-v-01e38c87><div class="view-section-title small" data-v-01e38c87>Step 2</div><ul data-v-01e38c87><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Preview and confirm the abstract you intend to submit</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Receive notification of acceptance in your email by May 15, 2025</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Pay your registration fee, abstracts from accounts that have not paid the registration fee will not be considered</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Edit your personal details if needed</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Check your registration status, especially during the important conference dates and deadline.</p></li></ul></div><div class="view-section" data-v-01e38c87><div class="view-section-title small" data-v-01e38c87>Formatting</div><ul data-v-01e38c87><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Please follow the formatting instructions below when submitting an abstract.</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Abstracts are restricted to 500 words (excluding title of abstract, authors’ names, addresses, and references), in Times New Roman font size 12, single line spaced. A template for the abstract can be downloaded <a href="./IJCSS_template_2012_AB.doc" download="IJCSS_template_2012_AB.doc" data-v-01e38c87>here</a>.</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Statements like “Data will be presented and discussed” is not acceptable.</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>The abstract should preferably contain original data. However, well-conducted systematic reviews/meta-analyses can be accepted.</p></li><li data-v-01e38c87><p data-v-01e38c87>Receipt confirmation of your abstract submission will be sent by e-mail.</p></li></ul><p data-v-01e38c87>Your registration will only be completed upon payment of your registration fee. Authors are welcomed to proceed with the payment after the acceptance of the paper to be presented in the Conference. All accepted abstracts will be compiled in a Book of Abstracts, which will be sent to authors after the presentation in the Conference Parallel Sessions.</p><p data-v-01e38c87>Authors whose papers meet the publication requirements of the association’s journal, <i data-v-01e38c87>International Journal of Computer Science in Sport</i> (IJCSS), will be invited to submit a full paper. The submission will undergo the regular submission process, peer review, and open-access publication by IJCSS. For details, please visit: <a href="https://sciendo.com/journal/IJCSS" target="_blank" data-v-01e38c87>https://sciendo.com/journal/IJCSS</a> (For Authors - Article Publishing Charges). Authors of other papers may also be invited to submit full papers (8-15 pages), which will be published by <strong data-v-01e38c87>Springer</strong> as part of the conference proceedings series <i data-v-01e38c87>Lecture Notes on Data Engineering and Communications Technologies</i> (EI).</p><p class="note" data-v-01e38c87>(Note: Only Accepted Abstracts will be considered for publication, after which you will be prompted to submit the short or full version of your paper).</p></div></div></div>',1),c=[s];function o(e,a,t,s,o,n){return(0,i.wg)(),(0,i.iD)("div",null,c)}var n={name:"SubmissionView"},r=t(89);const l=(0,r.Z)(n,[["render",o],["__scopeId","data-v-01e38c87"]]);var d=l}}]);
